WEBVTT

00:03.003 --> 00:04.569
[uneasy music]

00:04.613 --> 00:06.876
- [breathes shakily]

00:06.919 --> 00:12.882
♪

00:12.925 --> 00:14.623
Oh, my God.

00:14.666 --> 00:16.451
John, what happened in there?

00:16.494 --> 00:18.888
There's glass and blood
and--are you okay?

00:18.931 --> 00:20.542
- Oh, I'm never better, love.

00:20.585 --> 00:23.588
I'm finally feeling like
my old self again, you know?

00:24.807 --> 00:26.635
- What is up with you?

00:26.678 --> 00:29.899
- Oh, were you looking forward
to playing the nursing maid?

00:29.942 --> 00:32.554
I'm really sorry
to disappoint you.

00:32.597 --> 00:34.947
♪

00:34.991 --> 00:37.298
- Where the hell is Bishop?
- Sorry, what now?

00:37.341 --> 00:38.908
- Bishop stole Rory's comms.

00:38.951 --> 00:40.692
- 'Cause he knew John
was ripe for the picking.

00:40.736 --> 00:42.781
- So he smooth-talked
your boyfriend

00:42.825 --> 00:44.392
into springing him.

00:44.435 --> 00:46.437
Isn't that right, weasel?
- Oh, don't you worry

00:46.481 --> 00:48.352
your pretty little heads
about Bishop.

00:48.396 --> 00:49.875
Everything's in hand.

00:49.919 --> 00:51.486
- Uh, John,

00:51.529 --> 00:54.010
things feel decidedly
not in hand right now.

00:54.054 --> 00:55.707
- Do you know where Bishop is?

00:55.751 --> 00:58.841
Just tell us what happened.
We can help you.

00:58.884 --> 01:00.277
- How many times
do I have to tell you

01:00.321 --> 01:02.018
I don't want your help?

01:02.062 --> 01:03.715
[dramatic music]

01:03.759 --> 01:05.500
- I'm sorry, I'm--I'm confused.

01:05.543 --> 01:07.719
You said you wanted
to start a new life

01:07.763 --> 01:09.721
sans evil magical potion.

01:09.765 --> 01:11.854
Do--do you remember that
conversation we had?

01:11.897 --> 01:13.334
- Oh, yeah I remember.

01:13.377 --> 01:15.945
You see, but I had
a really good chin wag

01:15.988 --> 01:18.339
with Bishop, and then I finally
saw the way forward.

01:18.382 --> 01:19.818
- John, you have no idea

01:19.862 --> 01:21.603
how manipulative Bishop is,
all right?

01:21.646 --> 01:24.258
Please just tell us where he is
before it's too late.

01:24.301 --> 01:26.086
- He's promised to help me
unlock the Fountain,

01:26.129 --> 01:28.262
and that is a promise
that I intend to make him keep.

01:28.305 --> 01:29.872
- So you're just gonna
turn your back on all of us?

01:29.915 --> 01:31.439
- Oh, let's be honest.

01:31.482 --> 01:34.006
I was never one of you,
now, really, was I?

01:34.050 --> 01:36.052
A Legend.

01:36.096 --> 01:41.144
Nah, I'm a nasty piece of work,
and I walk my path alone.

01:41.188 --> 01:44.669
- John, this isn't like you.

01:44.713 --> 01:48.325
Deep down, I know you truly
care about this team.

01:48.369 --> 01:51.807
- Oh, come on, grow a pair,
will you, Gary?

01:51.850 --> 01:53.722
I'm not that pathetic,
little bastard

01:53.765 --> 01:55.637
that you used to know.

01:55.680 --> 01:57.726
- Yeah, you keep saying that

01:57.769 --> 02:01.033
over and over again
in different ways.

02:01.077 --> 02:02.470
He's stalling.

02:05.647 --> 02:07.997
- Ah! A ghost!

02:08.040 --> 02:09.216
- Astral projection.

02:09.259 --> 02:10.478
He's not here.

02:10.521 --> 02:13.872
- If he's not here, then...

02:13.916 --> 02:16.745
♪

02:16.788 --> 02:18.181
- The Legends
are onto our ruse.

02:18.225 --> 02:20.357
We need to leave now.
- Almost there.

02:20.401 --> 02:22.664
- If you reroute
my directory protocols,

02:22.707 --> 02:24.840
you'll short circuit
all communications and navig--

02:30.237 --> 02:31.760
- Okay, that's weird.

02:31.803 --> 02:33.544
- Yeah.
What the hell is going on?

02:33.588 --> 02:39.246
♪

02:39.289 --> 02:42.249
[exciting music]

02:42.292 --> 02:49.343
♪

02:53.912 --> 02:55.827
- All right, well,
that ain't England out there.

02:55.871 --> 02:59.004
- Gideon, who's flying
the ship?

03:00.658 --> 03:02.356
- Sara?

03:02.399 --> 03:04.096
Ava? Anyone?

03:04.140 --> 03:05.794
The comms are down.

03:05.837 --> 03:07.970
- All right, let's talk about
that ruddy plan.

03:08.013 --> 03:09.928
- Well, I'm more of
a fly-by-the-seat-of-my-pants

03:09.972 --> 03:11.191
kind of guy.

03:11.234 --> 03:13.584
- That's John and Bishop.

03:13.628 --> 03:14.933
No, no, no, no,
if it's us against

03:14.977 --> 03:17.153
John's dark magic,
we're gonna lose.

03:17.197 --> 03:19.373
- Yeah, but John--
- Permuto.

03:20.112 --> 03:22.114
- All right, lay it on me.

03:22.158 --> 03:23.899
What's next, J-Co?

03:23.942 --> 03:26.118
- Oh, you're gonna help me find
another place and time

03:26.162 --> 03:29.034
where the Fountain of Imperium
exists in history.

03:29.078 --> 03:31.123
- Ooh, I've always
been intrigued

03:31.167 --> 03:32.647
by the legend of the Fountain.

03:32.690 --> 03:35.258
Supposedly,
an enormous source of power

03:35.302 --> 03:37.173
gifted by a benevolent
alien being.

03:37.217 --> 03:39.262
- I encountered the Fountain
once before.

03:39.306 --> 03:43.397
It deemed me...unworthy.

03:43.440 --> 03:46.269
But then, if anyone can unlock
an ancient alien artifact,

03:46.313 --> 03:47.923
that's you, isn't it?
- Well...

03:47.966 --> 03:50.969
- I mean, it is the only reason
I set you free.

03:51.013 --> 03:53.885
- Oh, and here I thought

03:53.929 --> 03:55.452
you just wanted some company.

03:55.496 --> 03:59.282
[uneasy music]

03:59.326 --> 04:01.284
- I want my magic back

04:01.328 --> 04:04.853
without having to rely
on pesky drugs.

04:04.896 --> 04:08.900
Now, are you up to the task
or not?

04:09.858 --> 04:12.252
- Easy with the fire hands,
Johnny.

04:17.735 --> 04:20.738
I've spent a lifetime hacking
and editing alien genetics.

04:20.782 --> 04:25.526
Believe me, I am just
the super genius you need.

04:25.569 --> 04:28.224
- Good, let's get on
with it, then, shall we?

04:28.268 --> 04:32.533
♪

04:32.576 --> 04:34.491
[grunts]

04:34.535 --> 04:37.581
Apokalypste ti dynami.

04:40.454 --> 04:45.720
- Abracadabra, J.C.

04:45.763 --> 04:48.331
You've unveiled
sub-layers of alien texts

04:48.375 --> 04:49.811
hidden within the map itself.

04:49.854 --> 04:51.552
Nice.

04:51.595 --> 04:54.250
Lucky you, I'm versed
in dozens of alien languages.

04:54.294 --> 04:56.731
- Just read the bloody thing,
will you?

04:56.774 --> 04:59.777
- Now, that's interesting.
- What?

04:59.821 --> 05:01.344
- This symbol here

05:01.388 --> 05:04.304
might just give us a location
to the Fountain.

05:05.522 --> 05:07.176
- You see?

05:07.219 --> 05:10.310
You are up to the task,
sunshine.

05:10.353 --> 05:12.834
Let's chart a course.
- Eh.

05:12.877 --> 05:16.054
[dramatic music]

05:16.098 --> 05:22.931
♪

05:23.758 --> 05:25.629
- Okay, those two
working together

05:25.673 --> 05:27.457
to find the Fountain
is bad news.

05:27.501 --> 05:29.154
We have to go
and get the others.

05:29.198 --> 05:31.461
- Hell, I can't drive this ship
without Gideon.

05:31.505 --> 05:33.115
Can you?

05:33.158 --> 05:34.682
- I don't even have
a driver's license.

05:34.725 --> 05:38.555
- Then I guess it's up to us
to stop them.

05:44.605 --> 05:47.912
[engine sputtering]

05:47.956 --> 05:51.220
- Where the hell are we?

05:51.263 --> 05:52.961
1925?

05:53.004 --> 05:55.398
- And we're in Texas.
No wonder it seemed familiar.

05:55.442 --> 05:57.400
- Definitely explains
the yippee-ki-yay vibe.

05:57.444 --> 06:00.447
[man groaning]

06:02.666 --> 06:05.843
- Someone help, please!

06:05.887 --> 06:08.368
Henry will lose his leg.

06:12.154 --> 06:14.722
- Anyone?
- Oh, I can help.

06:14.765 --> 06:16.158
- What? Aliens?

06:16.201 --> 06:18.421
- No, something else.

06:18.465 --> 06:19.988
- Let me through.

06:20.031 --> 06:22.425
I can help, I can help.

06:22.469 --> 06:25.385
- There's something familiar
about her.

06:25.428 --> 06:26.864
- What is it?

06:31.956 --> 06:32.914
- Okay, okay.

06:32.957 --> 06:35.786
- I can't explain it.

06:35.830 --> 06:38.833
I think that's my mom.

06:43.838 --> 06:45.230
- The drilling line snapped.

06:45.274 --> 06:46.971
I tried to move fast, but--

06:47.015 --> 06:48.799
- Just try to hold
your leg still, okay?

06:48.843 --> 06:50.235
I'm gonna take care of you.

06:50.279 --> 06:51.236
I have something that
will help.

06:51.280 --> 06:52.673
- You're gonna be okay.

06:52.716 --> 06:55.110
- [groans]

06:55.153 --> 06:57.591
- It's gonna get worse
if you keep moving.

06:59.201 --> 07:01.464
- Oh, my Lord.

07:01.508 --> 07:03.423
It feels better already.

07:04.815 --> 07:06.426
- Get out of my way. Get!

07:06.469 --> 07:08.384
[ominous music]

07:08.428 --> 07:10.299
You look good to go, Henry.

07:10.342 --> 07:11.779
Back on the rig, now.

07:11.822 --> 07:13.345
- He needs to rest, Doc.

07:13.389 --> 07:14.956
- After his shift.

07:14.999 --> 07:17.480
Need that derrick
up and running by end of month.

07:17.524 --> 07:18.525
Let's go!

07:18.568 --> 07:24.400
♪

07:24.444 --> 07:26.271
Let me pay you
for your services.

07:26.315 --> 07:28.622
- No, I don't need
compensation.

07:28.665 --> 07:31.102
- Sure you do, sweetheart.

07:31.146 --> 07:34.192
Would me buying your land
cover it?

07:34.236 --> 07:36.978
- You know my answer.

07:37.021 --> 07:39.807
- If I don't buy your land,
someone else will.

07:39.850 --> 07:42.549
And they may not offer
as much as me

07:42.592 --> 07:44.681
or be as polite.

07:44.725 --> 07:46.422
- I have already told you

07:46.466 --> 07:49.860
my land is not for sale.

07:49.904 --> 07:51.819
- Maybe you ought reconsider.

07:51.862 --> 07:55.605
♪

07:55.649 --> 07:58.042
- She said no.

07:58.086 --> 08:00.305
- So why don't you get going,

08:00.349 --> 08:02.220
sweetheart?

08:03.483 --> 08:05.310
- [chuckles]

08:07.878 --> 08:09.750
I'll see you ladies around.

08:12.056 --> 08:14.319
- Thank you for your help.

08:14.363 --> 08:16.365
That man is a menace.
- Happy to.

08:16.408 --> 08:18.323
Dealt with plenty of men
like him in my lifetime.

08:18.367 --> 08:20.021
- I'm Gloria.

08:23.503 --> 08:25.069
Have we met?

08:25.113 --> 08:26.810
- We're just passing through.

08:26.854 --> 08:29.944
- Well, let me thank you
with a hot meal.

08:29.987 --> 08:32.163
Wouldn't be a proper
Odessa welcome otherwise.

08:32.207 --> 08:34.862
Hmm? Come.

08:34.905 --> 08:36.211
- Where are you going?

08:36.254 --> 08:37.473
We have to find
John and Bishop.

08:37.517 --> 08:38.822
- No, I can't.

08:38.866 --> 08:41.129
That woman, she's--
she's my mom.

08:41.172 --> 08:43.479
We're in Odessa, Astra,
my hometown.

08:43.523 --> 08:45.307
- I thought your mom
was abducted by aliens

08:45.350 --> 08:47.439
when you were a kid;
how could that possibly be her?

08:47.483 --> 08:50.312
- I don't know, maybe--
maybe they wiped our memories

08:50.355 --> 08:53.097
and they sent her back in time.

08:53.141 --> 08:55.491
That would explain
why I could never find her.

08:55.535 --> 08:58.102
- Hey, hey, hey.
I know you feel like

08:58.146 --> 09:00.104
you gave up on finding her
too easily,

09:00.148 --> 09:03.151
but I don't want you
to get your hopes up.

09:03.194 --> 09:05.806
- If there was a chance
that this was your mom,

09:05.849 --> 09:07.372
wouldn't you wanna
talk to her too?

09:10.245 --> 09:12.247
- [sighs]

09:12.290 --> 09:14.510
Fine. But maybe she knows

09:14.554 --> 09:16.077
something about the Fountain

09:16.120 --> 09:17.600
that can help us find
John and Bishop.

09:17.644 --> 09:19.384
- Are you coming?

09:23.345 --> 09:26.348
[high-pitched ringing]

09:26.391 --> 09:28.611
- The Fountain's near.

09:33.311 --> 09:36.227
No, no, no, no, no.
No, no, no, no, no!

09:36.271 --> 09:37.968
Bollocks!

09:38.012 --> 09:40.667
Looks like it's already
dried up, and that's because

09:40.710 --> 09:42.451
you got us here too late,
didn't you?

09:42.494 --> 09:45.759
- Or we've arrived
in the nick of time.

09:45.802 --> 09:48.196
Look at these
beautiful mushrooms.

09:48.239 --> 09:49.937
- What about
the bloody mushrooms?

09:49.980 --> 09:52.635
- Right, right, right.
Okay, you don't know this yet.

09:52.679 --> 09:54.376
Earthlings eventually discover
that mushrooms

09:54.419 --> 09:57.771
are actually
an ancient alien species.

09:57.814 --> 09:59.163
- So you're telling me
I've had aliens

09:59.207 --> 10:00.774
in my mushroom masala
this whole time?

10:00.817 --> 10:02.950
- Think about how weird
mushrooms are.

10:02.993 --> 10:05.169
There's nothing else like them
on Earth.

10:05.213 --> 10:07.781
And the caps on the ground,
just the tip of the iceberg.

10:07.824 --> 10:11.523
Most of the organism
is underground.

10:11.567 --> 10:13.700
What if--go with me on this.

10:13.743 --> 10:17.747
What if these mushrooms

10:17.791 --> 10:19.923
are connected to the Fountain?

10:19.967 --> 10:22.665
That could mean the Fountain
is, in fact, itself

10:22.709 --> 10:24.754
an actual alien being.

10:24.798 --> 10:26.713
- Ah...

10:26.756 --> 10:28.105
All of the Fountain's mythology

10:28.149 --> 10:29.716
is connected to caves
and grottos.

10:29.759 --> 10:31.326
I thought I was looking
for a body of water,

10:31.369 --> 10:33.894
but perhaps, just like
their alien cousins,

10:33.937 --> 10:36.244
the Fountain can
arise from the ground.

10:36.287 --> 10:40.074
- Finally,
someone who can keep up.

10:40.117 --> 10:42.119
If you can summon the Fountain,

10:42.163 --> 10:44.948
I can make sure it chooses you.

10:44.992 --> 10:46.254
I just need to take
some samples

10:46.297 --> 10:48.517
back to the ship, and voilà!

10:48.560 --> 10:50.824
We'll be synthesizing
with the Fountain in no time.

10:50.867 --> 10:53.174
- All right, let's get on
with it then, shall we?

10:53.217 --> 10:55.698
- [chuckling]

10:55.742 --> 10:58.788
[humming in distance]

11:01.791 --> 11:04.751
[soft music]

11:04.794 --> 11:11.845
♪

11:12.802 --> 11:14.891
- Please sit down.

11:14.935 --> 11:17.111
I will get us some tea.

11:17.154 --> 11:20.114
[warm music]

11:20.157 --> 11:27.208
♪

11:27.556 --> 11:30.602
- Have you been here awhile?

11:30.646 --> 11:33.388
- Since I was about your age.

11:33.431 --> 11:35.172
I built this house myself.

11:35.216 --> 11:36.652
- And this Doc guy,

11:36.696 --> 11:38.698
why is he so interested
in your land?

11:38.741 --> 11:40.917
- He says there's a fountain
of oil underneath it.

11:40.961 --> 11:44.268
My house is the last parcel of
land he hasn't scooped up yet.

11:44.312 --> 11:46.575
- Speaking of fountains,

11:46.618 --> 11:50.013
do you know
if there's one nearby?

11:50.057 --> 11:52.015
- No. Sorry, dear. No.

11:52.059 --> 11:54.844
- Where were you from
originally?

11:54.888 --> 11:57.847
- Los Arenales, El Salvador.

11:57.891 --> 12:00.023
That's my mother.

12:00.067 --> 12:01.982
She was a healer too.

12:02.025 --> 12:03.810
Taught me everything I know.

12:03.853 --> 12:05.594
I never thought I would leave,

12:05.637 --> 12:08.771
but my husband, Celso,
he died suddenly,

12:08.815 --> 12:11.948
and it was too painful
for me to stay.

12:11.992 --> 12:16.170
So I came here
to make a fresh start

12:16.213 --> 12:18.825
with my daughter.

12:18.868 --> 12:22.654
- Your--your daughter?

12:22.698 --> 12:25.745
- [humming]

12:30.662 --> 12:33.056
- Hello, there.

12:33.100 --> 12:34.362
- I'm warning you.

12:34.405 --> 12:36.233
Mama taught me how to fight.

12:36.277 --> 12:37.974
- Ah, did she now?

12:38.018 --> 12:40.194
Your mama's somewhere nearby,
is she?

12:40.237 --> 12:42.674
- We live just over that way.

12:42.718 --> 12:44.067
- I was just looking
at those mushrooms

12:44.111 --> 12:45.068
you're gathering there.

12:45.112 --> 12:46.722
- Why?

12:46.766 --> 12:48.811
Are you a healer?

12:48.855 --> 12:49.943
- You could say that, yeah.

12:49.986 --> 12:51.422
- My mom is a healer.

12:51.466 --> 12:52.902
That's why
I'm gathering these for her,

12:52.946 --> 12:54.861
but she's expecting me.

12:54.904 --> 12:56.732
I better go.

12:56.776 --> 12:58.212
- Can I show you a trick?

13:00.170 --> 13:03.130
[mysterious music]

13:03.173 --> 13:08.004
♪

13:08.048 --> 13:09.397
- Wow!

13:12.443 --> 13:13.618
You're magic!

13:13.662 --> 13:14.706
- Yeah, I am.

13:14.750 --> 13:16.926
Now, tell me,

13:16.970 --> 13:20.451
have you noticed anything else
growing in this forest

13:20.495 --> 13:23.150
even more magical
than those mushrooms?

13:25.979 --> 13:28.024
You're sure about that?

13:29.852 --> 13:30.853
Damn it.

13:32.899 --> 13:33.987
- Here.

13:34.030 --> 13:35.945
This is for you.

13:39.166 --> 13:41.385
Are you okay?

13:41.429 --> 13:43.300
- Yeah, yeah, I'm fine.

13:45.912 --> 13:47.261
What's your name?

13:49.350 --> 13:50.917
- Esperanza Cruz.

13:50.960 --> 13:57.271
♪

14:01.188 --> 14:04.017
- Look, your mom doesn't know
anything about the Fountain.

14:04.060 --> 14:06.410
Spooner, we have to go.

14:06.454 --> 14:09.109
- I can't leave yet.
If Gloria has a daughter,

14:09.152 --> 14:11.720
that's gonna mean that aliens
abducted me from here,

14:11.763 --> 14:14.679
wiped my memory,
and sent to me to the future.

14:16.377 --> 14:19.119
Look, if I'm right,
then any second now,

14:19.162 --> 14:21.034
kid-me is gonna walk
through that door.

14:21.077 --> 14:24.298
- Okay, well, maybe it's best
if kid-you doesn't see you-you

14:24.341 --> 14:27.301
for, I don't know,
timeline reasons.

14:27.344 --> 14:28.824
[door opens]

14:28.868 --> 14:31.174
- Mama!
- [speaking Spanish]

14:31.218 --> 14:38.007
♪

14:38.051 --> 14:40.401
- Mama, I met this man
who says he can heal people

14:40.444 --> 14:42.794
just like you can!

14:42.838 --> 14:44.535
- Good afternoon, ma'am.

14:44.579 --> 14:46.755
- Another healer.
What a coincidence.

14:46.798 --> 14:50.367
- What a coincidence indeed.

14:58.245 --> 15:01.422
- Don't worry,
we'll get John back.

15:01.465 --> 15:02.858
It'd be a lot easier
if we had a time courier.

15:02.902 --> 15:04.207
Why do we even bother

15:04.251 --> 15:05.600
taking those things off?
- Don't even--

15:05.643 --> 15:06.906
- My eggs are gonna hatch
without me.

15:06.949 --> 15:08.081
We need a plan.

15:09.691 --> 15:12.302
- Actually, we do know somebody
with a time ship

15:12.346 --> 15:14.870
that could help us. Gary!

15:14.914 --> 15:16.916
- Me?
- No, not you, dummy.

15:16.959 --> 15:18.743
Kayla.
We need you to contact her.

15:18.787 --> 15:20.658
- [laughs] No.

15:20.702 --> 15:22.138
No, no, no, no.

15:22.182 --> 15:24.140
That's a terrible idea.

15:24.184 --> 15:26.142
Are we taking a vote on this?
I vote nay.

15:26.186 --> 15:28.840
- Hey, Gary, listen to me.

15:28.884 --> 15:30.364
We need to stop John
from doing something

15:30.407 --> 15:33.236
more colossally stupid
than he already has.

15:33.280 --> 15:34.368
Go.

15:36.544 --> 15:38.372
- Okay.

15:38.415 --> 15:39.982
If we really
wanna get Kayla's attention,

15:40.026 --> 15:41.505
this is how we do it.

15:41.549 --> 15:42.854
- What the hell is that?

15:42.898 --> 15:45.031
- It's called an IGCOM.
- What?

15:45.074 --> 15:47.511
- It's an intergalactic
communication device.

15:47.555 --> 15:50.123
- So, sorry,
you're just gonna call Kayla?

15:50.166 --> 15:51.515
- Are you kidding?

15:51.559 --> 15:53.256
She would never answer my call.

15:53.300 --> 15:56.172
No, but there's something else
we can do with it.

15:58.044 --> 15:59.697
- Okay, Mick.

15:59.741 --> 16:01.743
Let's try to make this
a little more dynamic.

16:01.786 --> 16:03.571
Move your body
a little to the right.

16:03.614 --> 16:06.487
Other right. Yup, okay.
Just--chin down.

16:06.530 --> 16:08.358
Too much.
- Fake eggs coming in hot.

16:08.402 --> 16:10.491
- Oh, yeah. Okay.

16:10.534 --> 16:12.667
[quirky music]

16:12.710 --> 16:13.973
- This is worse
than giving birth.

16:14.016 --> 16:16.062
- Just sit still, okay?

16:16.105 --> 16:17.498
- Are you sure
this is gonna work?

16:17.541 --> 16:20.370
'Cause, uh...
- Oh, 100%.

16:20.414 --> 16:22.677
Kayla likes to pretend
she's never on Galixiposts,

16:22.720 --> 16:24.984
but she totally is,
and once we tag her,

16:25.027 --> 16:26.333
she's gonna lose it.

16:26.376 --> 16:28.161
- Okay, thank you, Gary.
- Okay, Mick.

16:28.204 --> 16:31.381
I think the only thing
left to do is smile.

16:31.425 --> 16:33.079
Be happy.

16:33.122 --> 16:34.384
- Okay, center him
in the photo.

16:34.428 --> 16:35.820
There we go.
- Right.

16:35.864 --> 16:38.649
- And picture.

16:38.693 --> 16:41.913
♪

16:41.957 --> 16:44.699
Tag Kayla.

16:44.742 --> 16:47.484
And post.

16:49.356 --> 16:51.575
And now we wait.

16:51.619 --> 16:53.447
- Wait? For how long?

16:53.490 --> 16:55.231
- Eh, you know,

16:55.275 --> 16:57.059
sometimes reception on Earth
can be a little spotty.

16:57.103 --> 16:58.582
- Oh, God.

16:58.626 --> 17:00.932
- Oh, my goodness,
how rude of me.

17:00.976 --> 17:02.282
I never got your names.

17:02.325 --> 17:03.631
- I'm Astra.

17:03.674 --> 17:06.808
- Esperanza,
but I go by Spooner.

17:06.851 --> 17:09.463
- Esperanza?
That's my name too.

17:09.506 --> 17:12.118
- Yes, and a beautiful one
at that.

17:12.161 --> 17:14.424
Tell me, what were you
looking for in the forest?

17:14.468 --> 17:16.078
- John.

17:16.122 --> 17:18.515
Oh, I was just foraging
for some medicinal herbs.

17:18.559 --> 17:19.951
- Are you sure you weren't
looking for something

17:19.995 --> 17:21.301
more poisonous?

17:24.304 --> 17:26.088
- "War of the Worlds"?

17:26.132 --> 17:28.395
- Mama and I read it together
every night.

17:28.438 --> 17:30.310
- That's a pretty scary book.

17:30.353 --> 17:32.442
- Space creatures aren't scary.

17:32.486 --> 17:33.965
- I want her to stay curious

17:34.009 --> 17:36.446
and keep her adventurous spirit
alive.

17:36.490 --> 17:38.709
- And I wanna travel
to other worlds.

17:39.928 --> 17:43.149
- I have a feeling you will.
- [laughs]

17:43.192 --> 17:44.759
- Okay, come help me
in the kitchen

17:44.802 --> 17:46.413
and tell me all about
the plants you found.

17:46.456 --> 17:48.502
- This is honey locust.
- Hmm.

17:48.545 --> 17:51.113
- You seem different.

17:51.157 --> 17:52.114
- What, you mean
not overburdened

17:52.158 --> 17:53.985
by guilt and remorse?

17:54.029 --> 17:56.423
- Why'd you show up here
with kid-me?

17:56.466 --> 17:58.686
- I found her while I was
looking for the Fountain.

17:58.729 --> 18:00.557
And do you know what?
It's a good thing that I did,

18:00.601 --> 18:03.647
because our chance encounter
gave me a wee glimpse

18:03.691 --> 18:05.258
into your past and her future.

18:05.301 --> 18:06.389
- Don't trust a word
out of his mouth.

18:06.433 --> 18:08.130
- I don't.

18:08.174 --> 18:09.827
- Is everything all right?

18:09.871 --> 18:11.394
- Everything's fine.
- You know, this can't wait.

18:11.438 --> 18:15.746
- Like hell it can't.
- Nunc somnum!

18:15.790 --> 18:17.008
- What did you do?

18:17.052 --> 18:18.445
- Never mind them.

18:18.488 --> 18:20.534
Come with me.

18:25.713 --> 18:27.410
- Boys!

18:27.454 --> 18:29.543
- Esperanza, run.

18:29.586 --> 18:31.719
Run, mi amor.

18:31.762 --> 18:34.765
[tense music]

18:34.809 --> 18:37.072
[screaming]

18:37.116 --> 18:39.205
- Mama!

18:39.248 --> 18:46.299
♪

18:57.136 --> 18:58.920
- Those men, they--they--

18:58.963 --> 19:00.791
- They kill your mom tonight.

19:00.835 --> 19:02.576
But you get saved
by the Fountain of Imperium.

19:02.619 --> 19:05.187
You see, it's not just
a source of raw power.

19:05.231 --> 19:06.710
It's an alien being
that whisked you off

19:06.754 --> 19:07.798
to keep you safe.

19:07.842 --> 19:10.061
It protected you, Spooner.

19:10.105 --> 19:12.063
- My whole life I thought
those aliens took my mom away,

19:12.107 --> 19:16.285
but really,
it was those oil men.

19:16.329 --> 19:18.505
- You have a choice.

19:18.548 --> 19:21.986
You can let history play out
as it did before.

19:22.030 --> 19:23.553
Or you can save your mother

19:23.597 --> 19:25.425
and your younger self
from those men.

19:25.468 --> 19:28.123
Esperanza never
has to leave here.

19:28.167 --> 19:30.865
She can have a normal life.

19:32.562 --> 19:34.173
- So what do you want from me?

19:42.442 --> 19:45.662
- My goodness, I don't know--
I don't know what came over me.

19:46.881 --> 19:49.057
Where did our guest go?

19:49.100 --> 19:50.450
- He sends his apologies.

19:50.493 --> 19:52.103
He has some business
to attend to.

19:52.147 --> 19:54.018
- Outside.

19:55.933 --> 19:58.153
What the hell did John do
in there?

19:58.197 --> 20:00.242
- He showed me the truth
about my past.

20:00.286 --> 20:02.984
The oil men come back
and kill Gloria for her land

20:03.027 --> 20:04.551
while kid-me escapes
and is saved

20:04.594 --> 20:06.553
by the Fountain of Imperium.

20:07.728 --> 20:09.991
So I'm staying here
and protecting them both

20:10.034 --> 20:12.602
to make sure that never
happens.

20:12.646 --> 20:14.952
- Look,
whenever John is involved,

20:14.996 --> 20:16.519
things tend to go south.

20:16.563 --> 20:18.304
- This is my only chance

20:18.347 --> 20:20.958
to make sure my younger self
has a life with my mom.

20:21.002 --> 20:22.264
I can finally get her back.

20:22.308 --> 20:25.267
That's all I've ever wanted.

20:25.311 --> 20:28.836
I thought you, of all people,
would understand that.

20:28.879 --> 20:31.969
- Of course I understand that,
Spooner, but...

20:36.713 --> 20:38.280
But you just gave
your blood to John

20:38.324 --> 20:40.369
to open the Fountain,
which is the one thing

20:40.413 --> 20:42.632
we are trying to stop.

20:42.676 --> 20:45.331
- You can go after him
if you want,

20:45.374 --> 20:47.333
but I'm staying here.

20:47.376 --> 20:53.208
♪

20:53.252 --> 20:55.341
- Are you sure
it actually posted?

20:55.384 --> 20:57.734
- Well, maybe we need
to check the Wi-Fi.

20:57.778 --> 21:00.694
[warbling, whooshing]

21:00.737 --> 21:03.958
- She's here.

21:06.003 --> 21:09.224
- [roars]

21:09.268 --> 21:11.922
- Kayla.
- [snarling]

21:11.966 --> 21:14.403
- Click-clack-clack.

21:16.753 --> 21:18.059
- What do you mean
they're fake?

21:18.102 --> 21:19.408
- We will explain.

21:19.452 --> 21:21.410
- [grunts]
- Look--

21:22.368 --> 21:24.979
We're sorry about the way
we had to contact you,

21:25.022 --> 21:27.068
but Bishop stole our ship,
and you are the only person

21:27.111 --> 21:28.678
that can help us get it back.

21:28.722 --> 21:30.158
- And why would I help
you guys?

21:30.201 --> 21:32.943
- 'Cause the eggs
on that ship are real.

21:32.987 --> 21:35.903
[soft music]

21:35.946 --> 21:38.253
♪

21:38.297 --> 21:39.602
- And how did you survive?

21:39.646 --> 21:41.691
- Miracle of childbirth.

21:41.735 --> 21:44.085
- Bishop acted as midwife
and saved Rory's life.

21:44.128 --> 21:47.480
♪

21:47.523 --> 21:48.655
- Those eggs are gonna
hatch soon.

21:48.698 --> 21:49.873
I have to go and protect them.

21:49.917 --> 21:51.353
- Wait.

21:51.397 --> 21:54.661
Ever since that night
on the planet,

21:54.704 --> 21:57.751
I've never stopped
thinking about you.

21:57.794 --> 21:59.230
The eggs might be fake,

21:59.274 --> 22:03.844
but my feelings for you
are...real.

22:07.630 --> 22:08.762
- The only thing
I care about right now

22:08.805 --> 22:10.938
is getting back my babies.

22:10.981 --> 22:13.680
- Well, if you wanna
get your eggs back from Bishop,

22:13.723 --> 22:16.900
you're gonna need our help.

22:22.471 --> 22:23.559
- What were you
little fellas doing

22:23.603 --> 22:25.779
in the Med Bay
all by your lonesome?

22:25.822 --> 22:28.521
Good thing you have me
to keep you company.

22:28.564 --> 22:32.133
[funky music]

22:32.176 --> 22:34.657
- I do hope that
that's a victory dance, Squire.

22:34.701 --> 22:38.792
- The groove is all part
of the process.

22:38.835 --> 22:42.404
Don't you worry, I got
the science covered, emo boy.

22:42.448 --> 22:44.232
You just make sure
your hocus is pocused.

22:44.275 --> 22:45.842
- Oh, don't you worry
about that.

22:45.886 --> 22:47.148
I have a sure-fire way
to summon the Fountain.

22:47.191 --> 22:48.454
- Oh.

22:48.497 --> 22:50.325
- What's all this malarkey
then?

22:50.369 --> 22:52.371
- This...

22:52.414 --> 22:55.417
this serum will temporarily
make every cell in your body

22:55.461 --> 22:58.507
mimic those of the most
angelic selfless child.

22:58.551 --> 23:01.423
- Which will make the Fountain
think that I am worthy.

23:01.467 --> 23:02.685
- Bingo.

23:02.729 --> 23:05.906
The serum will go into this,

23:05.949 --> 23:08.169
which I will hold onto
for safekeeping.

23:08.212 --> 23:09.823
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

23:09.866 --> 23:11.564
You just let me know
when it's all good and ready

23:11.607 --> 23:12.956
all right, squire?

23:13.000 --> 23:14.828
Good.

23:14.871 --> 23:17.831
[tense music]

23:17.874 --> 23:24.794
♪

23:24.838 --> 23:26.405
- John, do you really think

23:26.448 --> 23:28.015
Bishop is just gonna let you
use the Fountain?

23:28.058 --> 23:29.625
- Oh, don't be daft.

23:29.669 --> 23:31.105
I know he wants to use
the powers for himself,

23:31.148 --> 23:32.541
but old John Constantine
always has a plan.

23:32.585 --> 23:33.760
So do me a favor.

23:33.803 --> 23:35.675
Stay out of my way.
- No.

23:35.718 --> 23:37.416
Let me bring you back to
the team before it's too late.

23:37.459 --> 23:38.504
- "Oh, let me bring you
back to the team

23:38.547 --> 23:39.940
before it's too late, John."

23:39.983 --> 23:43.334
Don't bloody kid yourself.
Come on.

23:43.378 --> 23:46.512
You, of all people, understand
what I'm doing, don't you?

23:46.555 --> 23:49.645
You know what it feels like
to be powerless.

23:49.689 --> 23:52.039
To desperately need magic.

23:52.082 --> 23:54.128
- You've always had this
selfish streak in you,

23:54.171 --> 23:56.043
and my mom knew
it was dangerous.

23:56.086 --> 23:59.568
- Now, what would your mum
think about you now, eh?

24:00.395 --> 24:03.529
Her very own daughter
dabbling in the very dark arts

24:03.572 --> 24:05.313
that she ran away from.

24:05.356 --> 24:07.446
♪

24:07.489 --> 24:10.187
I think she'd be
turning in her grave.

24:10.231 --> 24:12.581
♪

24:12.625 --> 24:14.540
Vá embora.

24:16.106 --> 24:19.153
- [breathing heavily]

24:21.024 --> 24:22.809
Damn it, John.

24:27.683 --> 24:29.032
So what's your plan?

24:29.076 --> 24:30.512
Just gonna shoot them all?

24:30.556 --> 24:32.688
- How do you know
they're coming tonight?

24:32.732 --> 24:34.777
- Trust me, I know.

24:34.821 --> 24:36.562
[dramatic music]

24:36.605 --> 24:37.867
[gun clicks]

24:37.911 --> 24:40.479
♪

24:40.522 --> 24:43.569
[laughter]

24:43.612 --> 24:46.049
- Oh, Gloria!

24:46.963 --> 24:49.879
I've been playing nice, Gloria.

24:50.924 --> 24:53.187
Now I've come to the edge.

24:53.230 --> 24:55.102
So I'm gonna give you
five whole minutes

24:55.145 --> 24:57.017
to come on out here

24:57.060 --> 24:59.846
and sign your place over to me.

24:59.889 --> 25:01.717
- Just let me go talk to him.

25:01.761 --> 25:03.545
- It's a trap.

25:03.589 --> 25:06.243
They don't wanna talk.

25:07.636 --> 25:09.508
Is this the only gun you have?

25:09.551 --> 25:11.248
- I've never used it.
It belonged to Celso.

25:11.292 --> 25:13.424
I don't believe in
fighting with violence.

25:13.468 --> 25:16.558
I'm sure Doc and I
can come to a civil agreement

25:16.602 --> 25:17.777
and nobody needs to get hurt.

25:17.820 --> 25:19.605
[gunshot]

25:19.648 --> 25:21.781
- Mamí, what's going on?

25:21.824 --> 25:23.609
- Here, Esperanza.

25:23.652 --> 25:24.958
Why don't you read this
in the bedroom, okay?

25:25.001 --> 25:26.916
You'll be safer in there.

25:28.048 --> 25:29.832
- No!

25:29.876 --> 25:31.268
There will be
no bloodshed tonight.

25:31.312 --> 25:33.096
- There will be
if you don't fight them.

25:33.140 --> 25:34.315
- Why is this even
your business?

25:34.358 --> 25:37.361
- Because I'm your daughter!

25:37.405 --> 25:39.668
I lost you once, Mom.

25:39.712 --> 25:42.366
I'm not gonna lose you again.

25:45.021 --> 25:47.067
- My daughter?
- I know it sounds crazy,

25:47.110 --> 25:50.592
but it's me, Esperanza,
just all grown up.

25:50.636 --> 25:52.507
And because of some
insane circumstances,

25:52.551 --> 25:56.380
I've traveled from the future
to this moment in time.

25:56.424 --> 25:58.469
And I know that tonight
you and my younger self

25:58.513 --> 26:00.471
get separated
for the rest of our lives.

26:00.515 --> 26:03.300
- Separated? How?
- When those men attack,

26:03.344 --> 26:05.128
I lose you for good.

26:05.172 --> 26:06.521
And I escape into the woods

26:06.565 --> 26:08.175
only to end up
in a different time.

26:08.218 --> 26:12.048
[somber music]

26:12.092 --> 26:14.355
Please believe me.

26:14.398 --> 26:16.705
I can fix history.

26:16.749 --> 26:20.579
I can save you
and little Esperanza.

26:27.629 --> 26:30.589
- Esperanza.

26:30.632 --> 26:33.243
- It's me, it's me.

26:33.287 --> 26:36.203
And now that--
now that I'm here,

26:36.246 --> 26:38.771
you two can stay together.

26:38.814 --> 26:41.034
I'm going to protect you.

26:42.209 --> 26:44.864
[whispers]
I'm going to protect you.

26:44.907 --> 26:48.694
♪

26:53.176 --> 26:55.352
- Spooner.

26:55.396 --> 26:57.485
Remember if Esperanza
doesn't go to the Fountain,

26:57.528 --> 26:59.661
then you never come back
to save Gloria.

26:59.705 --> 27:01.445
- I'd rather protect her now

27:01.489 --> 27:04.492
so I can become the person
my mom always hoped I'd be.

27:04.535 --> 27:06.320
- If she does that,
then my little girl and I,

27:06.363 --> 27:08.365
we can stay together, yes?
- Yeah, you'll stay together,

27:08.409 --> 27:12.500
but history will be
completely changed.

27:12.543 --> 27:14.371
And you'll never
meet the Legends

27:14.415 --> 27:16.896
or help us save Sarah.

27:16.939 --> 27:19.289
You'll never become you,
Spooner.

27:19.333 --> 27:21.901
Which means that--

27:21.944 --> 27:25.687
which means we never
become friends.

27:25.731 --> 27:27.689
And I really don't wanna
lose my friend.

27:27.733 --> 27:30.126
[somber music]

27:30.170 --> 27:31.475
- I can't let
that innocent girl

27:31.519 --> 27:33.739
go through what I went through.

27:33.782 --> 27:36.480
- If Esperanza does go,

27:36.524 --> 27:38.569
she will grow up without me,

27:38.613 --> 27:40.571
but she becomes you,

27:40.615 --> 27:43.183
and history
will be preserved, yeah?

27:43.226 --> 27:46.708
♪

27:46.752 --> 27:50.016
Then Astra is right,
and we have no choice.

27:50.059 --> 27:52.801
Esperanzita has to go.

27:52.845 --> 27:57.284
- Losing you was the worst
moment of my life, Mom.

27:57.327 --> 27:59.155
I spent every day
trying not to think about

27:59.199 --> 28:00.548
what happened to you,

28:00.591 --> 28:02.724
and it only made me
angry and bitter.

28:02.768 --> 28:04.465
♪

28:04.508 --> 28:07.598
I didn't become the kind
of person you wanted me to be.

28:07.642 --> 28:10.210
Not even close.
- Yes, you did. You did.

28:10.253 --> 28:12.212
You became that person.

28:12.255 --> 28:13.300
You are brave.

28:13.343 --> 28:14.954
You have a big heart.

28:14.997 --> 28:19.045
You are a time traveler.

28:19.088 --> 28:21.830
Whether it's aliens
or the universe at play,

28:21.874 --> 28:24.398
you being here now
is not a coincidence.

28:24.441 --> 28:29.229
We were meant
to find each other again.

28:29.272 --> 28:31.535
Whatever powers took you away

28:31.579 --> 28:33.755
also brought you back to me.

28:33.799 --> 28:36.323
♪

28:36.366 --> 28:40.109
[speaking Spanish]

28:40.153 --> 28:42.068
♪

28:42.111 --> 28:44.897
- We're saved by faith alone.

28:44.940 --> 28:47.900
[uplifting music]

28:47.943 --> 28:49.771
♪

28:49.815 --> 28:51.991
- Stay with Gloria.

28:52.034 --> 28:55.385
I'll get Esperanza
to the Fountain.

28:58.693 --> 29:01.522
- Well, what do we do now,
magic man?

29:01.565 --> 29:04.046
Dance naked around a bonfire?

29:04.090 --> 29:06.005
Ooh, make a blood sacrifice,
perhaps?

29:06.048 --> 29:08.398
- Eh, we don't need
a sacrifice,

29:08.442 --> 29:10.966
but we do need blood.

29:11.010 --> 29:13.969
[tense music]

29:14.013 --> 29:20.671
♪

29:20.715 --> 29:25.720
Sit hoc sanguine, clavis est.

29:25.764 --> 29:31.682
♪

29:31.726 --> 29:34.120
- Ancient light show.

29:34.163 --> 29:36.644
You must have started
a chemical reaction

29:36.687 --> 29:38.298
which induced
a bioluminescent response

29:38.341 --> 29:40.213
in the cellular structure
of these mushrooms.

29:40.256 --> 29:42.693
- Would you stop your incessant
bloody commentary

29:42.737 --> 29:43.738
for one minute?

29:43.782 --> 29:47.133
[rumbling]

29:47.176 --> 29:54.227
♪

30:01.495 --> 30:03.497
Finally.

30:03.540 --> 30:05.673
There she is.

30:05.716 --> 30:08.676
[mysterious music]

30:08.719 --> 30:14.290
♪

30:14.334 --> 30:16.162
- Oh, Gloria!

30:16.205 --> 30:17.903
[tense music]

30:17.946 --> 30:20.993
- Everything is going to be
all right, mi amor.

30:21.036 --> 30:23.256
We've got to do what's right.

30:23.299 --> 30:29.392
♪

30:31.786 --> 30:33.919
Listen to me, mamíta.

30:33.962 --> 30:35.659
Astra, she's going
to take you somewhere.

30:35.703 --> 30:37.444
- Where?

30:37.487 --> 30:40.926
- Somewhere where
you'll be protected.

30:40.969 --> 30:43.667
I need you to be brave, okay?

30:43.711 --> 30:46.714
And to remember everything
I ever taught you.

30:46.757 --> 30:48.672
- Why do I have to go
without you, mamí?

30:48.716 --> 30:51.371
I don't want to go by myself.
- I know, honey.

30:51.414 --> 30:53.286
I don't want to either,

30:53.329 --> 30:56.289
but it's what we've got to do.

30:56.332 --> 30:57.899
And before you know it,

30:57.943 --> 31:01.207
we're going to see
each other again.

31:01.250 --> 31:04.471
And I know you can do it,

31:04.514 --> 31:08.692
my strong and fearless girl.

31:08.736 --> 31:11.217
- We're going to see
each other again.

31:11.260 --> 31:14.089
- I love you the most,
Esperanza.

31:14.133 --> 31:17.092
[somber music]

31:17.136 --> 31:19.051
♪

31:19.094 --> 31:21.314
- Time is up!

31:21.357 --> 31:23.185
You better come on out.

31:23.229 --> 31:25.187
- Okay. We have to go.
Come on.

31:25.231 --> 31:27.320
- Astra.

31:27.363 --> 31:28.799
Take care of me.

31:28.843 --> 31:29.931
♪

31:29.975 --> 31:30.932
- Always.

31:30.976 --> 31:37.983
♪

31:41.334 --> 31:44.598
- We've been doing this dance
far too long, Gloria.

31:44.641 --> 31:47.296
Just sign these papers,

31:47.340 --> 31:49.429
and we'll be on our way.

31:49.472 --> 31:51.953
- I'll say this once.

31:51.997 --> 31:53.824
This land belongs to me

31:53.868 --> 31:55.696
and to my daughter,

31:55.739 --> 31:58.351
and it is not for sale.

31:58.394 --> 32:01.006
- [chuckles]

32:01.049 --> 32:04.313
Why you ladies have to be
such a pain in my ass?

32:04.357 --> 32:05.793
Boys!

32:05.836 --> 32:07.099
[guns cocking]

32:11.842 --> 32:14.802
[dramatic music]

32:14.845 --> 32:21.896
♪

32:42.264 --> 32:44.005
What are you doing?

32:44.049 --> 32:46.007
- Showing you

32:46.051 --> 32:49.315
what real pain feels like.

32:49.358 --> 32:51.970
Because of your greed,

32:52.013 --> 32:55.016
you forced a young girl
to leave her mother

32:55.060 --> 32:56.887
and her home.

32:57.932 --> 33:00.195
I want you to feel the anger,

33:00.239 --> 33:02.067
the isolation,

33:02.110 --> 33:04.112
the anguish

33:04.156 --> 33:08.247
of losing everything
you've ever loved.

33:08.290 --> 33:11.032
♪

33:11.076 --> 33:13.295
- What the hell
are you waiting for?

33:13.339 --> 33:17.734
♪

33:17.778 --> 33:19.432
[groans]

33:21.434 --> 33:24.045
Who are you?

33:24.089 --> 33:27.092
- I am my mother's daughter,

33:27.135 --> 33:31.531
and this will never
be your land.

33:31.574 --> 33:34.403
- [groaning]

33:34.447 --> 33:38.190
♪

33:38.233 --> 33:40.409
[grunts]

33:41.671 --> 33:43.064
Ah!

33:43.108 --> 33:50.028
♪

33:57.383 --> 33:59.994
- John must have
opened the Fountain.

34:00.038 --> 34:01.778
- Is that where I'm going?

34:01.822 --> 34:05.217
- Yeah, sweetie,
that's where you have to go.

34:05.260 --> 34:07.741
- Will it be scary?

34:07.784 --> 34:09.960
- At first, yeah.

34:10.004 --> 34:11.440
But eventually,

34:11.484 --> 34:15.836
you are gonna find friends
and a family.

34:15.879 --> 34:17.316
And guess what.

34:17.359 --> 34:18.969
You're even gonna see me again.

34:19.013 --> 34:20.406
Kay?

34:20.449 --> 34:22.712
♪

34:22.756 --> 34:24.932
Esperanza, I need you to stay
here for a second, okay?

34:24.975 --> 34:28.805
♪

34:28.849 --> 34:30.503
Esperanza?

34:30.546 --> 34:32.809
- I told you
to stay out of my way.

34:32.853 --> 34:35.290
Suntok ni demonyo.

34:38.337 --> 34:40.556
- Hey, John-Boy?

34:40.600 --> 34:42.254
Is she part of the show?

34:42.297 --> 34:49.348
♪

35:03.797 --> 35:05.625
- What is it?

35:05.668 --> 35:07.453
- I can feel it.

35:10.020 --> 35:11.500
She's gone now.

35:14.851 --> 35:16.679
- No, she's right here,

35:16.723 --> 35:18.464
with me.

35:18.507 --> 35:25.558
♪

35:32.086 --> 35:35.133
[whooshing]

35:37.613 --> 35:39.789
- All right, losers,
we've located your ship.

35:39.833 --> 35:41.791
Odessa, Texas, 1925.

35:41.835 --> 35:44.185
- And the Fountain of Imperium
is in Texas.

35:44.229 --> 35:46.144
- I only care about my eggs.

35:46.187 --> 35:47.710
- The tracker says your ship
should be right in front of us,

35:47.754 --> 35:49.190
but I don't see it.

35:49.234 --> 35:52.237
- Oh, hold on. Wait. Uh...

35:52.280 --> 35:53.368
[lock chirps]

35:53.412 --> 35:54.804
And bingo.

35:54.848 --> 35:56.763
- There she is.
- Oh, I missed her.

35:56.806 --> 36:00.201
♪

36:00.245 --> 36:01.507
- Yeah.
- Oh, there she is.

36:01.550 --> 36:02.508
- Let's go.

36:02.551 --> 36:04.640
- Nate, wait.

36:04.684 --> 36:06.076
John's not gonna be
on that ship.

36:06.120 --> 36:08.296
All he cares about
is the Fountain.

36:08.340 --> 36:11.604
- Okay, so how do we find
a evil genius

36:11.647 --> 36:14.346
and a crazed wizard
in 1920s Texas?

36:14.389 --> 36:18.785
- Well, we, uh,
follow the weirdness.

36:18.828 --> 36:21.309
[mysterious music]

36:21.353 --> 36:24.312
- We need to act quickly
before the Fountain disappears.

36:24.356 --> 36:27.272
♪

36:27.315 --> 36:30.188
John, you snake.
You swiped the serum from me?

36:30.231 --> 36:31.885
- Yeah, well, I wasn't gonna
bloody well let you take it

36:31.928 --> 36:35.845
and have all those powers
to yourself, now was I?

36:35.889 --> 36:37.369
[vial clicks]

36:37.412 --> 36:38.370
[grunts]

36:38.413 --> 36:45.464
♪

36:45.942 --> 36:48.206
[whispering] Oh, yeah.

36:49.816 --> 36:51.992
I can feel it.

36:52.035 --> 36:54.081
I can feel the Fountain.

36:55.300 --> 36:58.346
[laughing]

37:00.609 --> 37:02.307
[coughs]

37:02.350 --> 37:03.656
- That's not exactly
the Fountain

37:03.699 --> 37:06.093
you're feeling, my friend.

37:06.136 --> 37:10.532
You see, the serum I cooked up
did indeed make you worthy,

37:10.576 --> 37:12.969
but I also added just a touch

37:13.013 --> 37:15.450
of deadly poison.

37:15.494 --> 37:18.453
[tense music]

37:18.497 --> 37:22.414
♪

37:22.457 --> 37:24.111
- There are the eggs.

37:27.332 --> 37:28.811
- It's locked!

37:28.855 --> 37:30.291
- Well, there's gotta
be another way in.

37:30.335 --> 37:32.075
- Gideon, are you there?

37:32.119 --> 37:35.122
- Guys, what is that thing
attached to the incubator?

37:36.210 --> 37:39.300
- Congratulations, Legends!

37:39.344 --> 37:41.737
You found your ship
and triggered this message.

37:41.781 --> 37:43.522
Now, I knew the first thing
you'd do is try to save

37:43.565 --> 37:47.352
these wonderful
interspecies eggs.

37:47.395 --> 37:49.136
But if you want them,
you'll have to play a game

37:49.179 --> 37:51.225
I call "48 Pick Up."

37:51.269 --> 37:54.533
Now, when I open the door,
you'll have scant few moments

37:54.576 --> 37:57.362
to gather as many of the eggs
as possible

37:57.405 --> 38:00.452
before the incubator
goes boom-boom.

38:00.495 --> 38:03.585
Starting...now.

38:04.630 --> 38:06.806
- Grab anything you can
to put the eggs into.

38:06.849 --> 38:09.983
[dramatic music]

38:10.026 --> 38:11.332
- Guys, hurry up!

38:11.376 --> 38:14.509
[timer beeping]

38:14.553 --> 38:19.427
♪

38:19.471 --> 38:22.517
- [gasps] Egg!

38:22.561 --> 38:25.607
[timer beeping]

38:25.651 --> 38:28.175
♪

38:28.218 --> 38:30.090
[beeping rapidly]

38:30.133 --> 38:34.224
[explosion blasts,
glass shatters]

38:34.616 --> 38:36.401
- Ugh, you bastard.

38:36.444 --> 38:38.577
- Oh, look, I'm sorry, John.
It's nothing personal.

38:38.620 --> 38:42.320
You're just collateral damage.

38:42.363 --> 38:44.147
Now that you're linked,

38:44.191 --> 38:47.063
killing you means
I destroy the Fountain.

38:47.107 --> 38:50.458
♪

38:50.502 --> 38:53.069
- Why?

38:53.113 --> 38:55.985
- To destroy the planet,
of course.

38:56.029 --> 38:58.466
You see, once upon a time,

38:58.510 --> 39:00.990
benevolent aliens
gifted the Fountain to Earth

39:01.034 --> 39:02.905
so it would act
as an invisible shield

39:02.949 --> 39:05.821
to protect the planet
from invasive alien species.

39:05.865 --> 39:07.997
- [groans]

39:08.041 --> 39:11.305
- I forgot to mention that,
didn't I?

39:11.349 --> 39:13.568
Once it dies,

39:13.612 --> 39:16.136
it's open season
on Earth, baby.

39:17.442 --> 39:20.923
I've tried
saving the planet twice,

39:20.967 --> 39:24.405
and humans just keep
getting in the way.

39:24.449 --> 39:26.668
♪

39:26.712 --> 39:28.801
Now I'm fast-forwarding
to the inevitable end

39:28.844 --> 39:31.978
so I can finally start anew.

39:32.021 --> 39:38.376
♪

39:38.419 --> 39:40.726
- [groans]

39:40.769 --> 39:42.118
- So long, Johnny.

39:42.162 --> 39:45.034
- [screams]

39:45.078 --> 39:52.128
♪

39:54.914 --> 39:57.786
- Something--
something's wrong.

39:58.961 --> 40:01.181
- [speaking Spanish]

40:01.224 --> 40:02.617
- [groans]
- Esperanza, que pasa?

40:02.661 --> 40:09.058
♪

40:09.102 --> 40:10.451
- John?

40:13.672 --> 40:15.717
John?
- Astra.

40:16.718 --> 40:18.677
Oh, I'm so--

40:18.720 --> 40:20.287
I'm so bloody sorry.

40:20.330 --> 40:22.245
- Just tell me what to do.

40:22.289 --> 40:24.552
There's gotta be a spell
that can help you.

40:24.596 --> 40:26.249
- Not this time.

40:26.293 --> 40:28.034
- No, you are John Constantine.

40:28.077 --> 40:29.383
You always have a plan.

40:29.427 --> 40:30.863
You have a trick
up your sleeve.

40:30.906 --> 40:32.560
- As luck would have it,

40:32.604 --> 40:34.780
I'm all out of tricks
this time.

40:34.823 --> 40:37.086
[somber music]

40:37.130 --> 40:39.654
You were my greatest failure...

40:39.698 --> 40:41.308
♪

40:41.351 --> 40:43.049
And my biggest accomplishment.

40:43.092 --> 40:46.574
♪

40:46.618 --> 40:48.010
God, you look like your mum.

40:48.054 --> 40:52.014
She would be so proud of you,
so proud.

40:52.058 --> 40:54.277
- No, no, John.

40:54.321 --> 40:56.584
John, I need you to try.

40:56.628 --> 40:58.368
I need you to stay alive.

40:58.412 --> 40:59.413
♪

40:59.457 --> 41:01.328
- [quietly] You hear that?

41:01.371 --> 41:03.330
[faint screaming]

41:03.373 --> 41:05.811
The screaming.

41:05.854 --> 41:07.247
♪

41:07.290 --> 41:10.293
It's the Fountain.

41:10.337 --> 41:11.860
I killed it.

41:11.904 --> 41:18.693
♪

41:18.737 --> 41:21.087
I killed it, Astra.

41:21.130 --> 41:23.524
♪

41:23.568 --> 41:25.613
- John!

41:25.657 --> 41:29.269
♪

41:29.312 --> 41:31.271
- I killed...

41:31.314 --> 41:38.365
♪

41:54.250 --> 41:57.210
[dramatic music]

41:57.253 --> 42:04.304
♪

42:13.269 --> 42:14.793
- Greg, move your head.
